<wpt lat="39.1070200727" lon="-110.6736846668"><ele>1596.0</ele><name>DP - Buckhorn Wash</name><desc>The canyon drive itself</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.123613" lon="-110.693904"><ele>1647.0</ele><name>DP - Buckhorn Wash Petroglyphs</name><desc>Famous 130-ft panel</desc><sym>petroglyph</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.1604974527" lon="-110.7292699814"><ele>1693.0</ele><name>DP - Dinosaur Footprint</name><sym>attraction</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.0985168307" lon="-110.7359099575"><ele>1583.0</ele><name>DP - Little Grand Canyon</name><desc>Combined with Wedge Overlook</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.0955288221" lon="-110.7490264424"><ele>1917.0</ele><name>DP - Wedge Overlook</name><desc>End-of-day highlight</desc><sym>binoculars</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.12445" lon="-110.75133"><name>[CAMP PRIMARY] May 3 (Sun) - Day 1: Black Dragon -&gt; Wedge - Wedge Overlook Campsite #5 (GPX) - cluster anchor (#3/#4/#5/#6/#7)</name><desc>$15/site honor system | None (no toilets, no water; very windy -- tie everything down) | First-come only. The 8 Wedge sites are spread along the rim road; #3 (39.12423,-110.74498), #4 (39.12748,-110.74781), #5 (39.12445,-110.75133), #6 (39.12254,-110.75204), #7 (39.12563,-110.75521) form a tight cluster. Scout ahead during Buckhorn Wash stop mid-afternoon; claim 3-4 adjacent sites for the group. 2.3-3.5 km N of track end at the overlook viewpoint. | Access: Wedge Rd spur off Buckhorn Draw Rd</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.12423" lon="-110.74498"><name>[CAMP PRIMARY-CLUSTER] May 3 (Sun) - Day 1: Black Dragon -&gt; Wedge - Wedge Overlook Campsite #3</name><desc>Designated site in the primary cluster anchored at Wedge Overlook Campsite #5 (GPX) - cluster anchor (#3/#4/#5/#6/#7)</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.12748" lon="-110.74781"><name>[CAMP PRIMARY-CLUSTER] May 3 (Sun) - Day 1: Black Dragon -&gt; Wedge - Wedge Overlook Campsite #4</name><desc>Designated site in the primary cluster anchored at Wedge Overlook Campsite #5 (GPX) - cluster anchor (#3/#4/#5/#6/#7)</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.12254" lon="-110.75204"><name>[CAMP PRIMARY-CLUSTER] May 3 (Sun) - Day 1: Black Dragon -&gt; Wedge - Wedge Overlook Campsite #6</name><desc>Designated site in the primary cluster anchored at Wedge Overlook Campsite #5 (GPX) - cluster anchor (#3/#4/#5/#6/#7)</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.12563" lon="-110.75521"><name>[CAMP PRIMARY-CLUSTER] May 3 (Sun) - Day 1: Black Dragon -&gt; Wedge - Wedge Overlook Campsite #7</name><desc>Designated site in the primary cluster anchored at Wedge Overlook Campsite #5 (GPX) - cluster anchor (#3/#4/#5/#6/#7)</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.10857" lon="-110.70223"><name>[CAMP BACKUP-A] May 3 (Sun) - Day 1: Black Dragon -&gt; Wedge - Wedge Overlook Camp #1 (GPX) - east-rim site</name><desc>$15/site honor system | None | East-side rim site, ~4.4 km E of the overlook. Designated Wedge site -- can be occupied on its own if the cluster is taken; good sunrise exposure but farthest from the iconic overlook viewpoint. | Access: Wedge Rd east spur (continue past the east-rim turn-off)</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.11221" lon="-110.73341"><name>[CAMP BACKUP-B] May 3 (Sun) - Day 1: Black Dragon -&gt; Wedge - Wedge Overlook Camp #2 (GPX) - east-rim site</name><desc>$15/site honor system | None | East-side rim site ~2 km WSW of #1, roughly midway between the east spur and the overlook. Also stands alone; pairs well with #1 if two rigs split east while the main group pushes the cluster. | Access: Wedge Rd east spur</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.11674" lon="-110.75523"><name>[CAMP BACKUP-C] May 3 (Sun) - Day 1: Black Dragon -&gt; Wedge - Wedge Overlook Campsite #8 (GPX) - southern outlier</name><desc>$15/site honor system | None | Southernmost Wedge site, on the same rim road as the #3-#7 cluster but ~900 m SSE. Use it to extend the cluster if we need one extra site, or as a standalone backup if the cluster is full. | Access: Wedge Rd spur, ~900 m before the main overlook turn-off</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.16753" lon="-110.73766"><name>[CAMP LAST-RESORT] May 3 (Sun) - Day 1: Black Dragon -&gt; Wedge - Buckhorn Draw Campsite 1 (GPX) - developed loop</name><desc>$15 ind / $50 group | Vault toilets, fire rings, tables | GPX has Buckhorn Draw sites 1, 7, 14, 15, 16, 17, 20, 23, 26, 30, 32. 32 total sites + 7 group sites. First-come despite Recreation.gov listing. ~8 km S of Wedge - requires backtrack at end of Day 1. | Access: Buckhorn Draw Rd, on route near mi 45-50</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.1155539228" lon="-110.854119549"><ele>1603.0</ele><name>River crossing</name><desc>Fuller Bottom ford of the San Rafael River (Upper San Rafael River WMA, BLM Fuller Bottom road = NF-3516 / BLM 6767, becomes Little Wedge Road / BLM 629 south of the crossing). Added per group request -- water crossings desirable for overlanders.</desc><sym>water</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="39.0139987505" lon="-110.8998799324"><ele>1719.0</ele><name>DP - The Drips</name><desc>Natural spring, on-route</desc><sym>natural-spring</sym></wpt>
