<wpt lat="38.8630858974" lon="-110.8679080009"><ele>2089.0</ele><name>DP - Eagle Canyon Overlook</name><sym>binoculars</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.860725" lon="-110.864991"><ele>2067.0</ele><name>DP - Eagle Canyon Bridges</name><desc>I-70 bridges from below</desc><sym>bridge</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.8578051481" lon="-110.8513368592"><ele>2025.0</ele><name>DP - Eagle Canyon Trail</name><desc>Trail section; full-size caution</desc><sym>off-road</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.848106" lon="-110.833328"><ele>2074.0</ele><name>DP - Eagle Canyon Arch</name><desc>Short walk</desc><sym>stone</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.8348605461" lon="-110.8108091354"><ele>2206.0</ele><name>DP - The Icebox</name><desc>Short walk into cool grotto</desc><sym>cave</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.835759" lon="-110.807499"><ele>2195.0</ele><name>DP - Swasey's Cabin</name><desc>Historic cabin</desc><sym>building-24</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.853001" lon="-110.803194"><ele>2189.0</ele><name>DP - Loan Warrior Petroglyph</name><desc>Short hike; panel sits ~1.5 mi off the main trail (spur drive budgeted in stop time)</desc><sym>petroglyph</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.7544645783" lon="-110.9243170904"><ele>1787.0</ele><name>DP - Reds Canyon</name><desc>Scenic drive-through</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.755407" lon="-110.948559"><ele>1767.0</ele><name>Lucky Strike Mine</name><desc>Mine of interest -- added to the route as a primary stop.</desc><sym>mine</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.68282" lon="-110.989"><name>[CAMP PRIMARY] May 4 (Mon) - Day 2: Wedge -&gt; Tomsich / Reds - Tomsich Butte Camp (GPX)</name><desc>Free (BLM) | None (no toilets, no water) | GPX waypoint &quot;Tomsich Butte Camp&quot; 1.98 km from track end. Open flat area near the uranium mine ruins and Hondu Arch trailhead. This is the logical end-of-day-2 camp. First-come / dispersed - Monday night should be open. | Access: Tomsich Butte Rd at the mine area</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.69237" lon="-110.99904"><name>[CAMP BACKUP] May 4 (Mon) - Day 2: Wedge -&gt; Tomsich / Reds - Dispersed Camp near Tomsich (GPX &quot;Camp&quot;)</name><desc>Free (BLM) | None | Adjacent GPX-marked camp spot ~1 km NW of Tomsich Butte Camp. Use if primary area is crowded; small footprint (2-3 rigs). | Access: Tomsich Butte Rd, 1 km past primary</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.76868" lon="-110.83217"><name>[CAMP LAST-RESORT] May 4 (Mon) - Day 2: Wedge -&gt; Tomsich / Reds - Family Butte Dispersed Camping (GPX) - BAIL EARLY option</name><desc>Free (BLM) | None | GPX-marked open dispersed area, room for 6-8 vehicles. ~15 km NE of Tomsich - use this if Day 2 runs long and you need to bail before reaching Tomsich Butte. Day 3 would then start with the Family Butte -&gt; Reds Canyon -&gt; Tomsich drive (~20 min) before the usual Day 3 agenda. | Access: Family Butte Rd spur, mid-route Day 2</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.683909739" lon="-110.9917396426"><ele>1579.0</ele><name>DP - Tomsich Butte Uranium Mine</name><desc>Mine ruins + equipment</desc><sym>mine</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6845382759" lon="-110.9988212585"><ele>1543.0</ele><name>[BACKUP] Hondu Arch Viewpoint</name><sym>binoculars</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6721088156" lon="-111.0157299042"><ele>2014.0</ele><name>DP - Hondu Arch</name><sym>stone</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.565817619" lon="-110.9536743164"><ele>1466.0</ele><name>DP - Hidden Splendor Overlook</name><sym>binoculars</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6072463252" lon="-110.8219671249"><ele>1660.0</ele><name>DP - Miner's Cabin</name><desc>Historic structure</desc><sym>building-24</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6174483344" lon="-110.8121358239"><ele>1733.0</ele><name>DP - Behind the Reef trail</name><desc>Technical trail section - slow</desc><sym>off-road</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6149456972" lon="-110.8025986551"><ele>1673.0</ele><name>[BACKUP] Little Wild Horse Canyon Trail</name><desc>LWH/Bell TH; skip OAB from Behind-the-Reef unless full ~8 mi LWH/Bell loop + party OK scrambling; FLASH FLOOD RISK — slot-canyon-guide.html</desc><sym>known-route</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6078020911" lon="-110.792877126"><ele>1645.0</ele><name>[BACKUP] Little Wild Horse Slot Canyon</name><desc>Full LWH/Bell loop waypoint only; same caveats — slot-canyon-guide.html</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6187227373" lon="-110.7610813765"><ele>1538.0</ele><name>[HIKE] DP - Chute Canyon</name><desc>Tactical slot/wash; easier; wide ~first mi; ~0.8 mi to first narrowing (GCT); partial OAB typical; see slot-canyon-guide.html + AllTrails Crack Canyon Wilderness</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.629651" lon="-110.763442"><ele>1567.0</ele><name>[BACKUP] Chute Canyon Trailhead</name><desc>Chute Canyon hike parking — slot-canyon-guide.html</desc><sym>known-route</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6323158128" lon="-110.7394259487"><ele>1632.0</ele><name>[HIKE] DP - Crack Canyon</name><desc>Tactical slot; ~5 mi RT typical (Utah.com); ~10 ft drop ~1 mi in; see slot-canyon-guide.html + AllTrails Crack Canyon Wilderness</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.643607" lon="-110.745181"><ele>1678.0</ele><name>[BACKUP] Crack Canyon Trailhead</name><desc>Crack Canyon hike parking; camping nearby possible — slot-canyon-guide.html</desc><sym>known-route</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.653784" lon="-110.676269"><ele>1722.0</ele><name>[HIKE] DP - Wild Horse Window Arch</name><desc>Default Day 3 hike; route author #1 geology; 2 mi RT; BLM not GSVP gate; set up camp before this hike and carpool to the trailhead; see slot-canyon-guide.html + AllTrails WHW</desc><sym>stone</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6503198742" lon="-110.6760708959"><ele>1599.0</ele><name>[BACKUP] Wild Horse Canyon</name><desc>AllTrails Wild Horse Canyon trail; lower priority — slot-canyon-guide.html</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.661013" lon="-110.669472"><ele>1633.0</ele><name>DP - Temple Wash Petroglpyphs</name><desc>Roadside panel (GPX name has a typo, kept exact for lookup)</desc><sym>petroglyph</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.65606" lon="-110.66015"><name>[CAMP PRIMARY] May 5 (Tue) - Day 3: Reds -&gt; Temple Mtn - Temple Mountain Townsite - Site 1 (Group Site) (GPX)</name><desc>$50/night | Vault toilets, fire rings, tables, large shade structure | GPX waypoint &quot;Site 1 (Group Site)&quot; - the Temple Mtn Townsite Campground group site. 1.43 km W of track end. First-come only. Tuesday night = very likely open. Scout during Behind-the-Reef slow section. | Access: Temple Mtn Rd, Townsite Campground complex</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.6577" lon="-110.66224"><name>[CAMP BACKUP] May 5 (Tue) - Day 3: Reds -&gt; Temple Mtn - Temple Mount East Campground (GPX)</name><desc>$15/site | Vault toilets | GPX waypoint &quot;Temple Mount East Campground&quot; - 10-site loop, 1.48 km from track end. First-come. Split group across several sites if group site is taken. | Access: Temple Mtn Rd, E of the Townsite</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.66075" lon="-110.64263"><name>[CAMP LAST-RESORT] May 5 (Tue) - Day 3: Reds -&gt; Temple Mtn - Dispersed &quot;Camp&quot; near track end (GPX)</name><desc>Free (BLM) | None | GPX waypoint &quot;Camp&quot; - CLOSEST GPX camp to Day-3 track end (0.58 km). Primitive dispersed. Multiple other GPX-marked dispersed spots within 3 km (e.g. 38.66500,-110.67681; 38.66549,-110.69267). | Access: On-route near Temple Mtn area</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.666217" lon="-110.6478182"><ele>1607.0</ele><name>DP - North Temple Wash</name><desc>Scenic narrows drive-through</desc><sym>cliff</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.8681032783" lon="-110.7791170217"><ele>2115.0</ele><name>Tunnel / Freeway Underpass</name><desc>HEIGHT CHECK for tall rigs; Freeway Access bypass if too tall</desc><sym>attraction</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.8807455" lon="-110.7710685212"><ele>2169.0</ele><name>DP - Head of Sinbad Petroglyph</name><sym>petroglyph</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.872668" lon="-110.787818"><ele>2135.0</ele><name>DP - Dutchman Arch</name><sym>stone</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.57563" lon="-109.52401"><name>[CAMP PRIMARY] May 6 (Wed PM) - Transit to Moab - Sand Flats Recreation Area — adjacent FCFS sites (cluster)</name><desc>Day-use + camping fees collected at booth | Picnic tables, fire rings, pit toilets; haul drinking water | No group reservation. Send scouts early afternoon if possible and grab adjoining numbered sites on the same loop (or neighboring loops). Up to **two rigs per pad** only when pads are large enough—trailers/tow combos usually need dedicated sites. | Access: Moab: Center/400 East -&gt; Mill Creek Dr -&gt; Sand Flats Rd (~5 mi graded)</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.471" lon="-109.745"><name>[CAMP BACKUP] May 6 (Wed PM) - Transit to Moab - Dead Horse Point SP - Wingate (electric site)</name><desc>$60/night | Electric, vault toilets, no showers | 150+ sites available May 6. One site fits up to 8. | Access: Hwy 313 W off Hwy 191</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
<wpt lat="38.65" lon="-109.77"><name>[CAMP LAST-RESORT] May 6 (Wed PM) - Transit to Moab - BLM designated dispersed pods (Mill Canyon / Cotter / Dubinky)</name><desc>Free where marked — obey posted waste rules | None (signs only) | Last resort north of Hwy 313 / east of Hwy 191; verify brown post sites. | Access: Spurs off Cotter Mine, Dubinky, Mill Canyon corridors</desc><sym>Campground</sym></wpt>
